## 2. User Journeys

### A. Oscar Sunday

- Host enters event (“2027 Oscars”); AI scaffolds all ballot categories.
- Group invite code/link is generated, shared via text.
- Friends join, see the leaderboard and categories, register in 1 tap, autofill if needed.
- Picks are **public immediately**—the mind game begins.
- As winners are announced, live Chatter erupts. Receipts and banter persist after the event.

### B. Bracket Challenge

- Host describes event (“2026 NCAA Lacrosse”), AI builds bracket.
- Group creates witty name, starts inviting more friends on the spot.
- “Autofill” option attracts casuals and outsiders.
- Deadline is drama moment—all picks lock, group history is sealed.
- Results entered, scoring triggers live leaderboard. Chatter is on fire.

### C. Survival Pool & More

- Supports event types: Survivor, Big Brother, F1 races, Drafts, etc.
- Platform nomenclature is neutral (Stage, Contender, Outcome, Chatter).

