## 3. Architecture & Tech Stack

- **Infra:** AWS primary, serverless preferred where suitable
- **Backend:** Node.js (Express/Koa), PostgreSQL (relational core), optional DynamoDB (high frequency feeds)
- **Frontend:** Next.js (mobile-first, SSR/ISR), React Native (future phase)
- **Real-time:** WebSockets (API Gateway/AppSync/Socket cluster)
- **AI:** Claude/GPT for event structure drafting
- **Auth:** JWT (AWS Cognito/Auth0/Clerk/custom)
- **Other:** Supabase used in early beta as backend

### Non-Negotiable Schema Rules:
- **Group-scoped picks:** enforced at DB, not just UI
- **Pick history:** pick changes tracked in separate table, visible post-lock
- **Recursive stages:** allows nesting for bracket/ballot/survival formats
- **No hard deletes:** soft delete (deleted_at) for all core entities
- **Real-time is not optional:** design for push, not polling

