## 4. Data Schema

### Relational (PostgreSQL):

- `events(id, title, format, deadline, created_by, status, created_at, tiebreak_method)`
- `stages(id, event_id, parent_id, title, stage_order, scoring_weight)`
- `contenders(id, stage_id, title, seed, metadata)`
- `groups(id, name, invite_code, created_by, created_at, streak_count, deleted_at)`
- `group_members(id, group_id, user_id, joined_at, role)`
- `picks(id, user_id, group_id, stage_id, contender_id, submitted_at, updated_at)`
- `pick_history(id, pick_id, user_id, group_id, old_contender_id, new_contender_id, changed_at)`
- `outcomes(id, stage_id, winner_contender_id, entered_by, entered_at)`
- `users(id, email, display_name, avatar_url, created_at, auth_provider)`
- `prop_questions(id, event_id, question_text, options, correct_option)`
- `prop_picks(id, question_id, user_id, group_id, answer, submitted_at)`
- `spectators(id, group_id, event_id, invited_by, spectator_email, invite_token, accessed_at)`

#### Key Indices & Constraints:
- One pick per user per stage per group: unique constraint at DB level
- Streaks, cross-event leaderboards pre-baked in schema for future roadmap

### NoSQL:

- `comments` (Chatter feed): group_id partition, event_id optional, id, body, created_at, user_id
- `reactions`: comment_id, user_id, vote, created_at
- `activity_feed`: group_id partition, id, event_id, user_id, activity_type, payload, created_at

