## 5. MVP Scope & Phases

### What **is** in MVP:
- Next.js frontend, Node + Postgres backend, JWT auth
- AI event builder (plain English → event structure)
- 2 event types at launch: bracket (NCAA Lacrosse), ballot (Oscars)
- Groups: create/join via invite code, persistent chat & history
- Per-group leaderboard, activity feed, real-time Chatter w/ reactions
- Pre-event pick visibility, pick change history “receipts”
- Prop question tie-breaker
- Spectator mode (invite-only, strictly read-only)
- Mobile-first: required for core screens

### What **is NOT** in MVP (for later phases):
- Native mobile apps, push notifications
- Public events, general user-generated events
- Monetization flows, advanced analytics
- Polymarket integration; only planned

**Phases:**  
- Week 1–2: Schema + DB lock, data migration  
- Week 2–3: Core application build, auth, real-time infra  
- Week 3–4: Groups feature (invites, group leaderboards/chatter)  
- Week 4–5: AI event creation  
- Week 5–6: Oscars event, prove generalization  
- Week 6–8: Engagement features, prop, autofill, beta test

